Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}, 1 tsp water (2 tsp for 4 servings), and @hot sauce{2%teaspoon} to taste. (Start with half the hot sauce, then taste and add more from there if you like things spicy.) Microwave until softened, ~{30%seconds}. Stir to combine.

Heat @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @diced chicken thighs{10%ounce} to pan with green pepper. Season with a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through and green pepper is tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} until combined. Turn off heat.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface.

Spread one half of each tortilla with half the spicy cream sauce (save the rest for serving). Using a #slotted spoon{}, top cream sauce with chicken filling, then sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create tortilla melts.

Wipe out pan used for filling. Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in same pan over medium heat.

Add tortilla melts (work in batches for 4); cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined cutting board{}.

Cut tortilla melts into wedges.

Divide between plates and serve with remaining spicy cream sauce on top or on the side for dipping.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.